  "text": "Firefox NSS TLS/SSL Implementation Audit - Core Protocol Files\n\nRepository: sg-evals/firefox--871325b8\nBase Directory: security/nss/lib/ssl/\n\nAUDIT FINDINGS:\n\n1. FILE: ssl3con.c (SSL 3.0/TLS Record Processing and Cipher Suite Negotiation)\n   Primary Protocols: SSL 3.0, TLS 1.0, TLS 1.1, TLS 1.2\n   Primary Functions:\n   - ssl3_HandleRecord: Processes incoming TLS records, including decryption, MAC verification, and content type dispatch (line 13721)\n   - ssl3_SendRecord: Implements record-level encryption and transmission for outgoing TLS records (line 2667)\n   - ssl3_NegotiateVersion: Negotiates the protocol version between client and server (line 1313)\n   - ssl3_SetupPendingCipherSpec: Sets up cipher specifications and key material for pending connections (line 1811)\n   Purpose: Core record layer processing for SSL 3.0 and TLS 1.0/1.1/1.2, handles record encryption/decryption, MAC computation, and cipher suite negotiation.\n\n2. FILE: tls13con.c (TLS 1.3 Handshake and Record Processing)\n   Primary Protocol: TLS 1.3 (RFC 8446)\n   Primary Functions:\n   - tls13_HandleClientHello: Processes client hello messages and manages early version negotiation\n   - tls13_HandleServerHello: Processes server hello messages and key share negotiation\n   - tls13_ComputeHandshakeSecrets: Computes handshake traffic secrets using HKDF-Expand-Label (line 1731)\n   - tls13_ComputeApplicationSecrets: Derives application traffic secrets for record protection (line 1804)\n   - tls13_SendKeyUpdate: Implements TLS 1.3 key update mechanism for traffic secret rotation (line 1148)\n   Purpose: Implements the complete TLS 1.3 handshake state machine, secret derivation using HKDF, and 0-RTT handling with post-handshake processing.\n\n3. FILE: dtlscon.c (DTLS-Specific Protocol Handling)\n   Primary Protocols: DTLS 1.0, DTLS 1.2, DTLS 1.3\n   Primary Functions:\n   - dtls_HandleHandshake: Processes fragmented DTLS handshake messages with sequence number tracking (line 274)\n   - dtls_FragmentHandshake: Fragments TLS handshake messages for UDP transmission with MTU awareness (line 679)\n   - dtls_TransmitMessageFlight: Transmits entire DTLS flight of messages with retransmission logic (line 815)\n   - dtls_StartRetransmitTimer: Implements exponential backoff retransmission timer for lost messages (line 948)\n   - dtls_HandleHelloVerifyRequest: Processes HelloVerifyRequest for cookie validation (line 1124)\n   Purpose: Handles datagram-based TLS (DTLS) specifics including message fragmentation, reordering, retransmission, and loss handling over UDP.\n\n4. FILE: ssl3ecc.c (ECC Cipher Suite Operations)\n   Primary Cryptographic Operations: ECDH (Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman) Key Exchange\n   Primary Functions:\n   - ssl_NamedGroup2ECParams: Converts named EC curve identifiers to SEC1/PKCS#1 EC parameters (line 35)\n   - ssl3_ComputeECDHKeyHash: Computes handshake message hash for ECDH signature validation (line 112)\n   Purpose: Implements elliptic curve operations for TLS cipher suites, specifically ECDH key agreement and EC signature schemes (ECDSA) used in modern TLS versions.\n\n5. FILE: sslexp.h (Experimental SSL APIs Header)\n   Purpose: Declares experimental and non-standard SSL APIs including:\n   - SSL_GetExtensionSupport: Query whether NSS supports specific TLS extensions\n   - SSL_EXPERIMENTAL_API macro: Safe dynamic dispatch mechanism for experimental features\n   - Extension validation and custom hook installation\n   This header provides a stable interface for applications to use experimental features while being resilient to API changes across NSS versions.\n\nSUMMARY:\nThese five files form the core of Firefox's NSS TLS/SSL protocol implementation, collectively supporting:\n- TLS 1.0 through TLS 1.3 (ssl3con.c, tls13con.c)\n- DTLS 1.0, 1.2, 1.3 (dtlscon.c)\n- ECC-based cipher suites (ssl3ecc.c)\n- Experimental/extensible APIs (sslexp.h)\n\nAll files are located in sg-evals/firefox--871325b8/security/nss/lib/ssl/ and are written in C (header files in .h format)."
}

